operation.parameter:
{
                "type": "object",
                "required": ["n_assets", "weights", "covariance_matrix"],
                "properties": {
                    "n_assets":          {"type": "integer",  "minimum": 2, "maximum": 2000,
                                          "description": "Number of assets in the portfolio"},
                    "weights":           {"type": "array",    "items": {"type": "number"},
                                          "description": "Exactly n_assets values. If normalize_weights=true they are scaled to sum=1 before calculation; otherwise caller must ensure they already sum to 1."},
                    "covariance_matrix": {"type": "array",    "items": {"type": "number"},
                                          "description": "Exactly n_assets×n_assets values, row-major order (element [i*n+j] is cov(i,j))"},
                    "normalize_weights": {"type": "boolean",  "default": false,
                                          "description": "Scale weights to sum=1 before calculation. Default: false — caller must supply weights that already sum to 1."},
                    "request_id":        {"type": "string",   "description": "Optional correlation ID echoed in the response"}
                }
            }

operation.description:
Calculate portfolio variance using covariance matrix multiplication.
Formula: σ²_p = Σ_i Σ_j w_i * w_j * σ_ij
This is an O(n²) operation that mirrors correlation calculations common in production financial risk systems.
Example JSON Request: { "n_assets": 500, "weights": [0.002, 0.002, ...], "covariance_matrix": [0.04, 0.006, ...], "request_id": "test-001" }
Example JSON Response: { "status": "SUCCESS", "portfolio_variance": 0.0156, "portfolio_volatility": 0.125, "annualized_volatility": 1.98, "calc_time_us": 4523, "memory_used_kb": 28456, "matrix_operations": 250000, "ops_per_second": 55273894, "device_info": "Android Device (Axis2/C 2.0 HTTP/2 JSON)", "comparison_note": "Java/WildFly requires 4-8GB RAM..." }

operation.parameter:
{
                "type": "object",
                "required": ["n_simulations", "n_periods", "initial_value", "expected_return", "volatility"],
                "properties": {
                    "n_simulations":   {"type": "integer", "minimum": 100,  "maximum": 1000000,
                                        "description": "Number of simulation paths"},
                    "n_periods":       {"type": "integer", "minimum": 1,    "maximum": 2520,
                                        "description": "Number of time steps (252 = 1 trading year)"},
                    "initial_value":   {"type": "number",  "description": "Initial portfolio value"},
                    "expected_return": {"type": "number",  "description": "Annualised expected return (e.g. 0.08 for 8%)"},
                    "volatility":      {"type": "number",  "description": "Annualised volatility (e.g. 0.20 for 20%)"},
                    "random_seed":     {"type": "integer", "description": "Seed for reproducible results. When omitted, seeded from time() — results differ across calls."},
                    "request_id":      {"type": "string",  "description": "Optional correlation ID"}
                }
            }

operation.description:
Run Monte Carlo simulation for Value at Risk calculation.
Simulates portfolio paths using Geometric Brownian Motion: S(t+dt) = S(t) * exp((μ - σ²/2)*dt + σ*sqrt(dt)*Z)
This is COMPUTE-INTENSIVE and demonstrates raw C performance advantage over JVM for numerical calculations.
Example JSON Request: { "n_simulations": 10000, "n_periods": 252, "initial_value": 1000000, "expected_return": 0.08, "volatility": 0.20, "random_seed": 12345, "request_id": "mc-001" }
Example JSON Response: { "status": "SUCCESS", "mean_final_value": 1082345.67, "var_95": 145678.90, "var_99": 234567.89, "cvar_95": 189012.34, "max_drawdown": 0.234, "prob_profit": 0.72, "calc_time_us": 234567, "simulations_per_second": 42650.5, "memory_used_kb": 31234 }

operation.parameter:
{
                "type": "object",
                "required": ["n_assets", "assets"],
                "properties": {
                    "n_assets":        {"type": "integer", "minimum": 1, "maximum": 2000,
                                        "description": "Number of assets"},
                    "assets":          {"type": "array",
                                        "minItems": 1, "maxItems": 2000,
                                        "description": "Array of asset scenario objects. Length must equal n_assets.",
                                        "items": {
                                            "type": "object",
                                            "required": ["asset_id", "current_price", "scenario_prices", "probabilities", "position_size"],
                                            "properties": {
                                                "asset_id":       {"type": "integer"},
                                                "current_price":  {"type": "number"},
                                                "scenario_prices":{"type": "array", "minItems": 2, "items": {"type": "number"},
                                                                   "description": "Price in each scenario. Must have equal length to probabilities."},
                                                "probabilities":  {"type": "array", "minItems": 2, "items": {"type": "number"},
                                                                   "description": "Probability weight per scenario (must sum to 1.0). Must have equal length to scenario_prices."},
                                                "position_size":  {"type": "number", "description": "Shares held (integer positions; fractional positions not supported by C implementation)"}
                                            }
                                        }},
                    "use_hash_lookup": {"type": "boolean", "default": true,
                                        "description": "Use O(1) hash lookup instead of O(n) linear scan"},
                    "request_id":      {"type": "string"}
                }
            }

operation.description:
Calculate scenario-weighted portfolio analysis.
Demonstrates hash table lookups vs linear search — the Array→Map optimization commonly applied in portfolio analytics code.
Example JSON Request: { "n_assets": 1000, "assets": [ { "asset_id": 12345, "current_price": 150.00, "scenario_prices": [165.0, 157.5, 150.0, 142.5, 135.0], "probabilities": [0.15, 0.25, 0.30, 0.20, 0.10], "position_size": 100 }, ... ], "use_hash_lookup": true, "request_id": "scenario-001" }

Get service metadata, capabilities, and current device statistics.
Returns information about: - Supported operations - Maximum limits (assets, simulations) - Current memory usage - Device/platform information - Comparison with Java/WildFly requirements
Example JSON Response: { "service_name": "FinancialBenchmarkService", "version": "1.0.0", "operations": ["portfolioVariance", "monteCarlo", ...], "max_assets": 2000, "max_simulations": 1000000, "memory_constraint_mb": 512, "current_memory_kb": 28456, "device_info": "Android Device (Axis2/C 2.0 HTTP/2 JSON)", "comparison_note": "This service runs on hardware..." }
